<h2 class="h2_Waypoints_blogpage" id="1_7">5 Best Places For River Rafting In Himachal Pradesh</h2>
<p>Himachal is known for its beautiful valleys, icy mountains, and stunning pastors. Here’s a list of some of the best river rafting town spots in the magnificent state of Himachal.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Manali</strong></li>
<li><strong>Kullu</strong></li>
<li><strong>Mcleod Ganj</strong></li>
<li><strong>Auli</strong></li>
<li><strong>Shimla</strong></li>
</ul>
<h3 style="font-family:Chaparral Pro Light;">1. Manali</h3>
<div><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-516813" src="./River Rafting In Himachal Pradesh 2022_ Know Everything Before You Go_files/Manali_27th-Feb.jpg" alt="Enjoying in Manali " width="700" height="401" srcset="https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Manali_27th-Feb-400x229.jpg 700w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Manali_27th-Feb-400x229.jpg 300w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Manali_27th-Feb-400x229.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"></div>

<p>Manali is a town enveloped with serenity, magnificence, and calmness. It has picturesque snow-capped peaks on one side, and turbulent river waters on the other. Manali is an excellent destination for all river rafting enthusiasts. This place is an ideal choice for adventure on all budgets and will be your best vacation ever. Before choosing to go to Manali for river rafting, always make sure to check the grade of river rafting a camp offers. You will feel ecstasy, calm, and breathless all at once in the best <a href="https://traveltriangle.com/blog/river-rafting-in-manali/">river rafting in Manali</a>. An excellent time to plan a Manali visit for river rafting should be between October to February when the weather is pleasant and bright.</p>
<p style="text-align: center"><strong></strong>
<h3>2. Kullu</h3>
<div><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-516809" src="./River Rafting In Himachal Pradesh 2022_ Know Everything Before You Go_files/Kullu_27th-Feb.jpg" alt="Kullu Trip with Friends" width="700" height="405" srcset="https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Kullu_27th-Feb-400x231.jpg 700w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Kullu_27th-Feb-400x231.jpg 300w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Kullu_27th-Feb-400x231.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"></div>

<p class="w3-serif">River rafting along the Beas river in Kullu is an unlimited fun experience. The clear waters of this river and its mild turbulence make this place a perfect destination for stream rafting. This is a great place to experience the panoramic view and culture of Kullu. Rafting season in Kullu begins in April and ends till June — just before there is an onset of monsoon. This place also offers grade 4 and grade 5 river rafting experience. This is a perfect adventure location for many thrillseekers who want to face the challenge against nature and emerge victoriously.</p>
<p style="text-align: center"><strong>
<h3>3. Mcleod Ganj</h3>
<p><em><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-518999" src="./River Rafting In Himachal Pradesh 2022_ Know Everything Before You Go_files/Best-Time-For-River-Rafting-In-Pahalgam-26-feb.jpg" alt="River Rafting In Pahalgam" width="700" height="400" srcset="https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Best-Time-For-River-Rafting-In-Pahalgam-26-feb.jpg 700w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Best-Time-For-River-Rafting-In-Pahalgam-26-feb.jpg 300w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Best-Time-For-River-Rafting-In-Pahalgam-26-feb.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"></em></p>
<p class="w3-serif">Tourists love McLeod Ganj for its lush green scenic views and chilly river waters of Chamba. River rafting in Chamba is a dream. This town has a Tibetan influence, and you will find a lot of Tibetan monasteries and architecture as you progress forward in river rafting. Mcleodganj offers grade 2 and grade 3 river rafting, and this is an excellent idea for all newbies. The best time to go river rafting in McleodGanj is during September, October, and November.</p>
<p style="text-align: center"><strong>
<h3>4. Auli</h3>
<p><em><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-531480" src="./River Rafting In Himachal Pradesh 2022_ Know Everything Before You Go_files/1024px-Alaknanda_River_Gochar_Uttarakhand_India.jpg" alt="alaknanda river" width="700" height="400" srcset="https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1024px-Alaknanda_River_Gochar_Uttarakhand_India-400x229.jpg 700w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1024px-Alaknanda_River_Gochar_Uttarakhand_India-400x229.jpg 300w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1024px-Alaknanda_River_Gochar_Uttarakhand_India-400x229.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"></em></p>

<p>River rafting in Auli on the Alaknanda river is a spiritual experience. The snow-capped mountains of Auli will leave you mesmerized. Alaknanda is the major tributary of Ganga and dissects Auli, and it’s a beautiful landscape. Auli has been a popular attraction for tourists from all over the world. River rafting in Auli is functional only for six months from October to March.</p>
<p style="text-align: center"><strong>
<h3>5. Shimla</h3>
<p><em><img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-531484" src="shimlar.jpeg" alt="" width="700" height="409" srcset="https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1024px-Tattapani_Hot_Springs_next_to_Sutlej_River_Himachal_Pradesh_India-400x234.jpg 700w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1024px-Tattapani_Hot_Springs_next_to_Sutlej_River_Himachal_Pradesh_India-400x234.jpg 300w, https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/1024px-Tattapani_Hot_Springs_next_to_Sutlej_River_Himachal_Pradesh_India-400x234.jpg 400w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"></em></p>

<p>Shimla offers one of the most challenging river rafting in Himachal Pradesh. Rafting is the Sutlej river in Shimla isn’t for newbies and requires a lot of prior experience. The stretches of river pass near Tattapani, which has sulfur springs of Himachal. The spreads offered here are 9 km,12 km, and 20 km. The cost of river rafting in Shimla is about 500 -1000 INR per person.</p>
